</gallery>

===Influence on ''Star Wars Rebels''===
McQuarrie's work has influenced the TV series ''[[Star Wars Rebels]]'' in multiple ways.

*The art style of ''Rebels'' is very similar to that of McQuarrie's concept art.<ref name="Rebels interview">{{WebCite|url=https://ew.com/article/2014/01/23/star-wars-rebels-interview|text='Star Wars Rebels': New series goes to dark places|author=James Hibberd|date=2014-01-24|work=''[[Entertainment Weekly]]''|archivedate=20181009211646}}</ref>
*The design of [[Lothal]] was based on some of McQuarrie's concept art.<ref name="Rebels interview" />
*The design of [[Garazeb Orrelios|Zeb]] and his species, the [[Lasat]], were based on early [[Chewbacca]] art done by McQuarrie.
*A man based on an early McQuarrie design of "General Skywalker" can be seen seated behind [[Sabine Wren]] in the episode "[[Droids in Distress]]."
*The design of [[Azmorigan]] was based on early [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure|Jabba the Hutt]] art done by McQuarrie.
*The character [[Quarrie]], introduced in the episode "[[Wings of the Master]]," is named after McQuarrie.
*The [[Moyn]] are based on a rough sketch for an alien bounty hunter in ''The Empire Strikes Back''.<ref name="SW-The Call Episode Guide &#124; Star Wars Rebels">{{SW|url=series/star-wars-rebels/the-call-episode-guide|text="The Call" Episode Guide &#124; Star Wars Rebels}}</ref>
*The stylized version of Darth Vader is a reference to McQuarrie's one, also used on the cover of the first edition of [[Star Wars: A New Hope (novelization)|the novelization of ''A New Hope'']].
*The [[E-XD-series infiltrator droid|E-XD infiltrator droids']] standard forms resemble C-3PO's original concept art.

===Influence on ''Star Wars: The Bad Batch''===
*The [[TK stormtrooper armor]] was based on McQuarrie's early Stormtrooper armor designs.

